wikipedia_page.main: William Keen (born 1792 at Godalming, Surrey; died 26 June 1846 at Godalming) was an English amateur cricketer who played first-class cricket from 1821 to 1831.  He was mainly associated with Surrey and made 28 known appearances in first-class matches, including three for the Gentlemen between 1824 and 1830.

response: William Keen (1680s–1754) was a merchant and judicial officer in the British colony of Newfoundland.
